BMW Reaches 2012 Component Spending Cut Target, Auto News Says

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-03-12T09:22:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-12/bmw-reaches-2012-component-spending-cut-target-auto-news-says.html
  Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW) ’s
target of cutting spending on components by 4 billion euros
($5.6 billion) by 2012 has already been reached,  Automotive News 
Europe said, citing Herbert Diess, the company’s head of
purchasing.  The German automaker will now focus on innovation and
quality, the newspaper cited Diess as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
